<subSubSection id="8B8F2DA2A73D2CE6EC94A1ABCB3B536B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F6C549B380CFC85F518688A5B59E116A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B3A17A1B09121AF788A8B43C69C95A99" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A common Old World weedy species recorded as an adventive in the Caribbean region.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="707B2993B685EA2F634E14B5CD01C340" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="F26A7276AA2A3FC2150DA900207CC22F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">PUERTO RICO.</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="D505393DCC168B202F92A9526865112A" originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
Piedras, 
<emphasis id="D4D19407A8B24ED694E42F79772CE3BC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">J.A. Stevenson</emphasis>
2278 (K, NY).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="666A8BFB2B372FCD22110A1B8D96A534" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="C5F91C392EBEC26AC765FA2CA4785188" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">LESSER ANTILLES. St Vincent</emphasis>
: &quot;Rev. L. G.&quot; (K).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BC19DEE156F08A30870B15A38071C056" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="52C36D104DDB253B502C9EC319E9288B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D67B06EA079811FEFED434BAD9F35043" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A rather distinct Old World annual species because of its small hirsute flowers, ovate acuminate sepals that are spreading in fruit, and hirsute capsule. It is the only representative of an Old World Clade found in the Neotropics.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
